There was a mild drama at the Federal High Court, Abuja, on Friday as presiding judge, Justice Abang Okon,  told the embattled former Chairman of the Pension Reform Task Team, Abdulrasheed Maina, to stop looking at him. Okon stated this when he was about to rule on the application for bail filed by Maina's lawyer , Ahmed Raji. Okon said,  "Please I don't want the 1st defendant to look at me when I am delivering my ruling so that I can concentrate."  



